South Africa’s Borrowing Costs Declined at Debt Auction, Central Bank Says

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-08-02T09:11:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/south-africa-s-borrowing-costs-decline-at-central-bank-debt-auction.html
South Africa ’s borrowing costs fell
at a central bank auction of 2.1 billion rand of debt maturing
in 2017 and 2031, according to the Pretoria-based Reserve Bank’s
data on Bloomberg.  The Pretoria-based Reserve Bank today sold 1.3 billion rand
of 8.25 percent bonds due 2017 at an average yield of 7.77
percent, 36 basis points, or 0.36 percentage point, lower than
at the previous auction on July 19. It auctioned 800 million
rand of 7 percent notes due 2031 at an average yield of 8.68
percent, 27 basis points lower than at the previous auction on
July 12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in Cape Town at 
